Prevention of complications in surgical management of back pain and sciatica.
 Accurate diagnosis of lumbar disc disease requires a thorough examination.
 Appropriate neurodiagnostic studies are required to confirm the suspected diagnosis.
 Other diagnoses should be considered prior to surgery, especially when there is a lack of correlation between the history, physical examination, or radiologic investigation.
 Proper surgical techniques should also help in preventing complications and are further discussed in this article.
